Database Setup & Migration Guide
Follow these steps to set up your local PostgreSQL database and apply the schema for Increment 1.

1. Prerequisites
Ensure you have PostgreSQL installed and running.
Mac: brew install postgresql
Windows: Download the installer from postgresql.org

2. Create the Database:
Create the official development database named f1_predictor.

# Drop it first if it exists (fresh start):
dropdb f1_predictor --if-exists

# Create the new database:
createdb f1_predictor

3. Configure Environment
Create a .env file in the backend/ directory (if you haven't already) and add your connection string
# inside backend/.env
# Replace YOUR_USER and YOUR_PASSWORD with your local postgres credentials
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://YOUR_USER:YOUR_PASSWORD@localhost:5432/f1_predictor
There is a .env.example file, you can use that to make your own .env with your own credentials and rename it 

4. Run Migrations
Run Alembic to read the migration file and create the tables (drivers, races, teams, etc.).
# Run from the 'backend' directory:

alembic upgrade head


Run these commands to confirm the tables were created successfully.
1. Check Alembic Status
This confirms the database is on the latest revision:

alembic current
Success: You should see a hash code ending in (head).

2. List the Tables
This confirms the schema was applied:

psql f1_predictor -c "\dt"
Success: You should see a list of tables including circuits, drivers, races, teams, etc.

